no-this-before-super.description:
Description

This rule is aimed to flagthis/superkeywords beforesuper()callings.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-this-before-super: "error"*/

class A1 extends B {
    constructor() {
        this.a = 0;
        super();
    }
}

class A2 extends B {
    constructor() {
        this.foo();
        super();
    }
}

class A3 extends B {
    constructor() {
        super.foo();
        super();
    }
}

class A4 extends B {
    constructor() {
        super(this.foo());
    }
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-this-before-super: "error"*/

class A1 {
    constructor() {
        this.a = 0; // OK, this class doesn't have an `extends` clause.
    }
}

class A2 extends B {
    constructor() {
        super();
        this.a = 0; // OK, this is after `super()`.
    }
}

class A3 extends B {
    foo() {
        this.a = 0; // OK. this is not in a constructor.
    }
}
